-- Persian Gulf Stocks: Damas International and First Gulf Bank
-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 2012-01-04T10:49:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-04/persian-gulf-stocks-arabtec-holding-and-damas-international.html
Abu Dhabi ’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI) 
advanced 0.3 percent to 2,416.61 at the 2 p.m. close in the
emirate, the highest since Dec. 14. Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI) 
slipped 0.3 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Damas International Ltd. (DAMAS)   surged to the highest
in more than two years, soaring 13 percent to 26 cents. The
Dubai-based jewelry maker and retailer said its majority
shareholders, the Abdullah Brothers, appointed a financial
adviser to sell part of their stake in the company for no less
than 45 cents a share.  First Gulf Bank PJSC (FGB)   gained as much as 1 percent
to 15.65 dirhams before closing at 15.55 dirhams, the highest
since Dec. 18.  JPMorgan Chase & Co. (JPM)  said the lender controlled
by Abu Dhabi’s ruling family may pay a higher dividend in 2011
and this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
